datosLaboralesPOJO.descripcion: A laboratory research position at the Joint Research Laboratory of the Hungarian Academy of Sciences & the Semmelweis University. Roles included routine cell culture methods, cytotoxicity assays, cell vitality and cell size detection studies, RNA isolation and quality control, PCR techniques, transfection and cell array technologies, and supervising of undergraduates.
Discovery Early Career Researcher Award (DECRA) holder from the Australian Research Council to conduct the research project Forensic genomic toolkit for tracking the illegal parrot trade.
Researching stories for BBC super-landmark natural history series.

datosLaboralesPOJO.descripcion: Responsible for all the logistics and operations of the TRC eco-lodge located in the most remote region of the South-eastern Peruvian Amazon. Role included coordination of boats, trainings, maintenance, staff, yearly budget of the lodge, etc. Supervised more than 30 employees.

Designing and administering the website of a scientific research project. Also leading their marketing operations and public outreach. Recruiting volunteers and coordinate their permits and participation in the project in Peru.

Responsible for all research activities at the Tambopata Research Center in the breeding season of 2008. Coordination and management of the research, supervising national and international volunteers. Training them for research activities like clay lick observation, parrot census, foraging studies, climbing trees, measuring chicks at artificial and natural nests, capturing wild macaws for veterinary examination and satellite collaring, etc.
